  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "d5RC/ymfZfTZ9y1ZH/WlsB/rQJI=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Storage and recovery feature set:\n- **AES-256-GCM encryption** at the app layer for operations and manifests.\n- **Hierarchical feeds**: user \u2192 drive \u2192 document, letting the reader walk the tree lazily.\n- **Folder topology preserved** across sync, recovery, and sharing.\n- **Manifest compaction** \u2014 old op batches are merged so recovery is fast even after long history.\n\nSharing (ACT-protected):\n- **Encrypted drive bundles** shared between users via Swarm IDs.\n- **ECDH-based access control** through Swarm's native ACT (Access Control Trie). The Bee node handles decryption transparently, so the app layer does not perform any shared-secret math itself. This avoids a whole class of app-layer key-exchange bugs and delegates the crypto boundary to a well-audited primitive.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
